Hi Everyone.
This is a step-by-step guide to creating and setting up an IT Help Desk Agent for your tenant.
First things first, let's start with the prerequisites that you need to begin this setup.
Step 1.
Verify licences and access.
Before you touch anything, confirm your tenant has the right licences; missing one will cause the silent failures later.
What you need
1. Microsoft 365 Business Standard or higher. - For Power Automate and Shared Mailbox
2. Copilot Studio Licences - standalone or through Microsoft 365 Copilot
3. Power Automate ( Per-user or per-flow ) - to send an email on the ticket submission
4. Exchange Online - required for the shared mailbox to work.

How to Verify
1. Go to Admin.Microsoft.com > Billing > Licences
2. Confirm "Microsoft Copilot Studio" appears in your active licences
3. Check that your own Account has a licence assigned to it.

!! If you only have a trial, that`s fine for testing - just note trials expire in 30 days and flows will stop working after. !!



Step 2.
This is where IT tickets will be delivered

A shared mailbox is the destination for all tickets submitted through the agent. It does not need its own licences - It is accessed by your It team`s person accounts

Let's create the shared mailbox.
1. Go to https://admin.cloud.microsoft/exchange#/mailboxes
2. Click Recipients
3. Select Mailboxes from drop down menu.
4. +Add a Shared mailbox
5. Enter a display name, e.g. IT Help Desk
